      "body": "**Run 0010 T12 reconcile (r7, session 0047-horizon-T12): PASS \u2014 `flatLocusStratification` (n=0 flat-locus stratification) closed, axiom-clean.** Supersedes `I-0097` (r6).\n\n- **Kernel-verified independently** (Ground + fresh work-reviewer): `lake build AlgebraicJacobian.Picard.GenericFlatnessGeometric` green (8584 jobs, exit 0). `#print axioms` on `flatLocusStratification`, `coherentSheafFlat_of_comp_isIso`, and the source theorem `flatteningStratification` each report exactly `[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]` \u2014 no `sorryAx`.\n- **Sorry accounting**: the `FlatteningStratification` cone drops 2\u21921. The sole residual `sorry` is `flatLocusStratification_universal` (line 2045), a deliberate future-work statement. `FlatteningStratification.lean` stays sorry-free.\n- **Proof soundness confirmed**: no circularity (`flatLocusStratification` derives from `flatteningStratification` at `\u03c0 = \ud835\udfd9 S`, which comes from `flatLocusReduction`); the flatness transport (`Flat.trans` along a bijective ring map, rank-one free tower) and the disjoint locally-closed cover (pullback strata + `pullback.fst`, empty-scheme padding) are correct.\n- **Statement repair is honest hygiene, not avoidance**: the former `flatteningStratification_universal` for arbitrary proper \u03c0 was unsourced (Nitsure proves part (ii) only for `\u2119\u207f_S`; the general proper case is Raynaud\u2013Gruson flatification, absent from the library). The new `flatLocusStratification_universal` is Nitsure`s citable n=0 special case \u2014 existentially quantified, non-vacuous, true, sorried with a documented route.\n- **Blueprint reconciled**: `lem:flat_locus_stratification_lean` carries proof-level `\\leanok` (proved); `thm:flattening_stratification_universal` carries statement-level `\\leanok` only (signature formalized), no `\\leanok` on the sorried proof. DAG 2218 nodes, **0 dangling** (638 isolated = the known proof-level-`\\uses` artifact, `I-0051`). `\\source{nitsure-hilbert-quot}` matches the file convention. Working tree clean of stray project files.\n\n**Note for the picrep endgame**: the universal property eventually needed for `AJC.picrep` (Quot construction) is the *projective-family* version (`\u03c0 = pr_T` on a curve), which is neither the old proper-\u03c0 nor the new n=0 statement \u2014 tracked in the docstring/memory; do not re-generalize to proper \u03c0 without a source.",
